WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.000
Downloaded From AnimeArcadia.lk

00:05.980 --> 00:07.063
[helicopter whirring]

00:17.105 --> 00:18.480
[White Rabbit] Bloodstryke,

00:20.271 --> 00:21.771
you're still alive.

00:23.396 --> 00:24.396
Good.

00:25.146 --> 00:27.646
I have use of you.

00:28.146 --> 00:29.480
[chilling music intensifies]

00:29.563 --> 00:30.396
[music halts]

00:30.480 --> 00:31.313
[wet spattering]

00:31.396 --> 00:34.105
[gnashing, chomping]

00:36.771 --> 00:38.771
[eerie, distressing music playing]

00:40.938 --> 00:42.188
[sharp cry]

00:42.271 --> 00:43.271
[groans]

00:43.355 --> 00:45.105
[overwhelming metal music pounding]

00:45.188 --> 00:47.188
[wet, discomforting gurgling]

00:58.271 --> 01:00.146
[White Rabbit snarling]

01:08.021 --> 01:10.021
["Rollin' (Air Raid Vehicle)"
by Limp Bizkit playing]

01:10.105 --> 01:12.271
♪ Your… your… your hands up ♪

01:12.355 --> 01:15.021
♪ Your… your… your hands up ♪

01:15.105 --> 01:17.771
♪ Throw your hands up
Throw your hands up ♪

01:17.855 --> 01:20.271
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

01:20.355 --> 01:22.938
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

01:23.021 --> 01:25.646
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

01:25.730 --> 01:27.813
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

01:27.896 --> 01:30.605
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

01:30.688 --> 01:33.021
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

01:33.105 --> 01:35.521
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

01:35.605 --> 01:38.021
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

01:38.105 --> 01:40.230
♪ Hey, ladies, hey, fellas ♪

01:40.313 --> 01:43.105
♪ And the people that don't give a **** ♪

01:43.188 --> 01:45.271
♪ All the lovers, all the haters ♪

01:45.355 --> 01:48.105
♪ And all the people
That call themselves players ♪

01:48.188 --> 01:50.188
♪ Hot mommas, pimp daddies ♪

01:50.271 --> 01:53.188
♪ And the people rollin' up in Caddies ♪

01:53.271 --> 01:55.688
♪ Hey, rockers, hip-hoppers ♪

01:55.771 --> 01:57.938
♪ And everybody all around the world ♪

01:58.021 --> 02:00.688
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

02:00.771 --> 02:03.188
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

02:03.271 --> 02:05.396
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

02:05.480 --> 02:08.271
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

02:08.355 --> 02:10.480
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

02:10.563 --> 02:13.063
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

02:13.146 --> 02:15.771
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

02:15.855 --> 02:16.855
[song trails off]

02:34.813 --> 02:35.980
[groaning]

02:36.063 --> 02:38.188
Do you always do this after your missions?

02:38.271 --> 02:40.605
Usually when I kill a demon, I just…

02:41.105 --> 02:42.980
I don't know, leave them there.

02:43.480 --> 02:47.063
I know. How do you think all those bodies
stay hidden from the public?

02:47.855 --> 02:48.688
Huh.

02:49.563 --> 02:51.146
[soldier] Jesus.

02:51.813 --> 02:53.396
What are we doing here, sir?

02:53.896 --> 02:57.021
Lay the bodies face up, weapons in hand.

02:57.521 --> 03:01.521
We need to have the media's
front page photo waiting for them.

03:02.813 --> 03:05.563
So, what are you
planning to do with that amulet?

03:06.063 --> 03:07.855
Carry it around in your pocket?

03:07.938 --> 03:10.855
That depends
on whether you're gonna try to take it.

03:10.938 --> 03:11.938
I'm not.

03:12.605 --> 03:13.980
You're gonna give it to me.

03:14.063 --> 03:15.480
Aren't we past all this?

03:15.563 --> 03:17.313
We fought an army together, sorta.

03:17.813 --> 03:19.771
I saved your life three times.

03:19.855 --> 03:21.646
-Twice.
-Two and a half.

03:22.605 --> 03:25.521
The White Rabbit won't be
the last to come after that.

03:25.605 --> 03:27.271
You really think you can protect it?

03:27.355 --> 03:29.646
I'm the only one that can protect it.

03:29.730 --> 03:31.938
Who else do you trust with it? That guy?

03:32.855 --> 03:37.188
Yes. Baines is willing to do
what's necessary to protect this realm.

03:37.271 --> 03:40.438
Seems to me
like he hasn't actually done anything.

03:40.521 --> 03:43.896
Besides giving orders that ended
with a whole lot of you dead.

03:43.980 --> 03:45.896
Which he doesn't look too torn up about.

03:45.980 --> 03:47.396
You don't know him.

03:47.480 --> 03:49.771
He's hard because he has to be.

03:49.855 --> 03:50.855
But he cares about…

03:52.188 --> 03:53.188
his people.

03:55.646 --> 03:59.480
Mr. Vice President, sir. Not to ask
questions above my pay grade here,

03:59.563 --> 04:01.896
but what are these things?

04:01.980 --> 04:03.646
What did this to them?

04:03.730 --> 04:06.896
What they are
will be revealed soon enough.

04:06.980 --> 04:09.271
As for what did this…

04:09.355 --> 04:10.355
She did.

04:11.355 --> 04:12.730
[soldier] That girl?

04:12.813 --> 04:14.896
[Baines] More of a trained attack dog.

04:14.980 --> 04:18.396
Brimming with anger and violence
that serve their purpose.

04:19.271 --> 04:22.646
Though sometimes
she must be brought to heel.

04:23.313 --> 04:25.438
[peculiar, mysterious synth music playing]

04:39.563 --> 04:43.105
If you don't want to
give me that amulet, fine.

04:43.188 --> 04:44.480
I say one word,

04:44.563 --> 04:46.521
and the soldiers you're surrounded by

04:46.605 --> 04:49.521
blow your brains right through
that fucking haircut.

04:49.605 --> 04:53.105
Yeah, because it worked so well
the last time you sent 50 guys at me.

04:53.188 --> 04:55.105
Then I'll do it myself.

04:55.688 --> 04:57.355
[Enzo chortling suggestively]

04:57.438 --> 04:59.771
I'm feeling it between you two.

04:59.855 --> 05:04.730
Do I sense a former prisoner-captor
romance vibe happening here?

05:04.813 --> 05:05.646
[chuckles]

05:05.730 --> 05:08.688
Out of the two prisoners,
I can't believe you went with him.

05:08.771 --> 05:09.896
I kid, I kid.

05:11.313 --> 05:12.313
[clears throat]

05:13.063 --> 05:14.896
Listen, Dante.

05:15.605 --> 05:18.688
If it's about a job,
my prices have tripled.

05:19.688 --> 05:22.313
So you're still taking jobs from me?

05:22.396 --> 05:23.730
Yeah, why not?

05:23.813 --> 05:26.980
I can always count on you to sell me out
for the slightest bit of personal gain.

05:27.480 --> 05:28.855
Hard to find someone that reliable.

05:29.438 --> 05:30.646
That's great to hear.

05:30.730 --> 05:34.230
I was talking to a few of these
government types on the ride over here

05:34.313 --> 05:36.021
about a sweet demon-killing--

05:36.105 --> 05:37.230
[Baines] Lieutenant Arkham.

05:38.105 --> 05:40.105
Where is Sparda's sword?

05:40.813 --> 05:43.605
The Rabbit took it with him
into the river, sir.

05:43.688 --> 05:45.730
Failing to secure your objectives…

05:45.813 --> 05:48.605
That disappointment I could accept.

05:48.688 --> 05:52.396
But you have caused me
to doubt your devotion, Mary.

05:53.021 --> 05:56.896
I know. My team was killed
because I led them into the Rabbit's trap.

05:56.980 --> 06:00.605
-Whatever reprimand you deem fit--
-This isn't about your team.

06:00.688 --> 06:03.063
They served the purpose God intended.

06:03.771 --> 06:07.021
Our fight is for humanity's souls.

06:07.105 --> 06:09.230
Every vessel is expendable.

06:09.813 --> 06:11.188
The amulet.

06:11.271 --> 06:13.480
Tell me you at least secured that.

06:13.563 --> 06:16.188
[distressing music warbles]

06:16.771 --> 06:19.396
The Rabbit took the amulet with him too.

06:19.480 --> 06:23.230
If you guys could drop it by my place
when you find it, that'd be great.

06:23.313 --> 06:24.146
You remember where.

06:25.063 --> 06:26.480
Is that what happened?

06:26.563 --> 06:29.396
I was poisoned. Paralyzed.

06:29.480 --> 06:31.230
From my position, it was hard to see.

06:32.896 --> 06:35.980
It doesn't matter.
The Lord will provide what we need.

06:36.063 --> 06:39.646
We didn't go looking for this war,
but it's here.

06:39.730 --> 06:43.605
You're running a whole paramilitary
operation to hunt and kill demons.

06:43.688 --> 06:45.438
I think you looked for it pretty hard.

06:45.521 --> 06:48.980
I told you, Dante, that you may have
a chance to earn your redemption.

06:49.063 --> 06:51.938
This is your war too, by blood.

06:52.021 --> 06:53.521
You need to choose a side.

06:53.605 --> 06:56.105
I'm not much of a war guy.

06:56.188 --> 06:58.605
Call when you piss off
an actually powerful demon

06:58.688 --> 07:00.188
and make things even worse.

07:00.271 --> 07:01.480
Sure it won't be too long.

07:01.563 --> 07:03.855
All units, on target.

07:05.480 --> 07:08.188
You can't have thought
that someone with your power

07:08.271 --> 07:10.396
would be allowed to just walk free.

07:11.146 --> 07:14.563
-Lieutenant, take the demon into custody.
-[Mary] Sir--

07:14.646 --> 07:17.396
That was what an order sounds like.

07:18.730 --> 07:20.730
[tense music escalating]

07:24.396 --> 07:25.646
[distant boom]

07:29.355 --> 07:30.355
[heavy footfalls thudding]

07:33.813 --> 07:35.355
[menacing music playing]

07:41.563 --> 07:42.730
[shocked clamoring]

07:44.396 --> 07:46.938
Fire! Fire on the new target!

08:10.646 --> 08:11.688
[gasps]

08:12.480 --> 08:14.480
[gunfire in distance]

08:17.980 --> 08:21.271
Holy macaroni! What is that thing?

08:22.146 --> 08:23.771
Those tubes in his body!

08:23.855 --> 08:25.355
Yeah, it's the Rabbit.

08:25.980 --> 08:26.855
How?

08:26.938 --> 08:30.396
Whatever the recommended dose is
for 'roiding yourself up with demon blood,

08:30.480 --> 08:33.355
I think he just
drastically fucking exceeded it.

08:36.271 --> 08:38.105
Hey! Down here!

08:53.521 --> 08:54.730
[chuckles grimly]

09:01.146 --> 09:03.521
Hey, Enzo,
that guy looks kind of dangerous.

09:03.605 --> 09:05.813
You might want to get somewhere safe.

09:06.396 --> 09:08.646
Ha, so reliable.

09:14.271 --> 09:15.855
[rowdy rock music playing]

09:31.730 --> 09:34.563
Where are those anti-demon bullets
you keep shooting me with?

09:34.646 --> 09:36.813
These are anti-demon bullets.

09:36.896 --> 09:39.855
His DNA must still be
too human to detonate them.

09:40.521 --> 09:43.563
Or we haven't tried
shooting him enough yet.

09:51.813 --> 09:53.605
Okay, it's a DNA thing!

10:02.771 --> 10:03.771
[energy humming]

10:07.855 --> 10:09.355
[rowdy rock music continuing]

10:22.480 --> 10:23.438
[snarls]

10:32.230 --> 10:34.480
It might take me
more than one punch to beat him now.

10:34.563 --> 10:38.188
All his demon blood runs through
a valve from that thing on his chest.

10:38.271 --> 10:40.855
We have to shoot the valve
and cut off the power supply.

10:40.938 --> 10:44.021
Eh. Think the gun you gave me
was defective.

10:44.105 --> 10:45.605
You're not getting another one.

10:47.980 --> 10:49.605
[regulator burbling]

10:55.271 --> 10:56.271
Lady!

10:57.271 --> 10:58.938
[screaming]

11:02.688 --> 11:06.313
How do you manage
to get even uglier each time I see you?

11:06.396 --> 11:08.188
It's actually impressive.

11:08.896 --> 11:13.188
Give me… the amulet!

11:13.271 --> 11:14.980
[frenetic metal music playing]

11:27.105 --> 11:28.480
Think, Enzo. Think!

11:38.063 --> 11:39.688
[Dante] Not as easy as it looks, is it?

11:39.771 --> 11:41.063
Turning into a demon.

11:41.771 --> 11:43.855
I don't think your body
can take this for long.

11:43.938 --> 11:48.563
It just needs to be long enough!

12:09.855 --> 12:11.188
[Enzo] Hey!

12:13.396 --> 12:15.605
Ugly rabbit freak!

12:15.688 --> 12:16.771
[Dante gasps]

12:18.980 --> 12:22.813
I've got your gateway to Hell right here!

12:22.896 --> 12:23.813
[blade piercing flesh]

12:23.896 --> 12:24.896
[grunts]

12:25.480 --> 12:27.063
[regulator burbling steadily]

12:30.688 --> 12:31.980
No!

12:32.813 --> 12:35.896
Should have been hiding in a hole
like the vermin you are.

12:37.063 --> 12:38.063
[Enzo moans]

12:38.146 --> 12:39.521
[Dante sputtering]

12:39.605 --> 12:42.396
[shakily] Enzo, why did you do that?

12:42.980 --> 12:44.480
[chuckling raggedly]

12:45.271 --> 12:46.396
You see?

12:46.896 --> 12:51.605
[weakly] I told you
I would take a blade for you.

12:52.896 --> 12:54.896
[delicate, distressing music playing]

13:04.021 --> 13:05.063
Enzo…

13:06.355 --> 13:08.271
[steely, raucous music building]

13:10.813 --> 13:12.021
[energy crackling]

13:13.563 --> 13:15.188
[chuckles slyly]

13:16.646 --> 13:18.896
[frenetic electronic music pulsing]

13:34.521 --> 13:35.688
[bracelet trills]

13:37.438 --> 13:38.438
[bracelet drones]

14:10.896 --> 14:13.396
[frenetic electronic music intensifying]

14:18.230 --> 14:20.188
[White Rabbit] That's all I needed.

14:21.146 --> 14:22.355
[helicopter whirring]

14:25.438 --> 14:26.813
[screams]

14:26.896 --> 14:27.813
[revving]

14:31.521 --> 14:33.230
[Mary] Hellblood! Let's go!

14:37.980 --> 14:38.896
[distorted whooshing]

15:14.271 --> 15:15.188
[alarm trilling]

15:31.438 --> 15:33.438
[helicopter alarm blaring]

15:46.438 --> 15:48.438
[groaning, coughing]

15:50.438 --> 15:51.771
[frenetic music subsiding]

15:51.855 --> 15:52.855
[groaning weakly]

15:56.605 --> 15:58.688
[White Rabbit chuckling grimly]

16:01.521 --> 16:03.021
Finally…

16:13.355 --> 16:15.855
The Sword of Sparda…

16:19.396 --> 16:21.063
in its true form.

16:22.396 --> 16:23.855
Look at it.

16:24.480 --> 16:31.063
This spectacle of prosperity,
built on the misery of an unseen world.

16:31.563 --> 16:37.646
It ends the moment I let this blade
touch the blood of Sparda's entire line.

16:37.730 --> 16:39.355
[Dante laughing]

16:40.230 --> 16:41.896
The entire line?

16:41.980 --> 16:44.396
You need the blood of the entire line?

16:44.980 --> 16:48.646
Why didn't you say that before?
We could have just skipped all of this.

16:48.730 --> 16:51.021
See, that would mean you also need--

16:51.105 --> 16:53.521
Blood from Vergil.

16:55.146 --> 16:57.146
[White Rabbit cackling]

17:00.855 --> 17:02.313
[Dante] How did you…

17:02.396 --> 17:03.938
Vergil is…

17:04.021 --> 17:05.021
[White Rabbit] Dead?

17:05.105 --> 17:09.813
No, Dante.
Your other half is very much alive.

17:10.396 --> 17:12.438
That's impossible.

17:12.521 --> 17:13.855
I… I watched him die.

17:13.938 --> 17:17.105
[sardonically] Oh, did you?

17:24.980 --> 17:26.355
Tell me.

17:26.438 --> 17:30.605
How does it feel
to be reunited with your brother?

17:37.896 --> 17:39.438
[energy pulsing]

17:49.105 --> 17:50.730
[maelstrom thrumming]

17:54.938 --> 17:56.771
[dark, ominous music playing]

18:06.813 --> 18:08.521
[civilians yelling]

18:09.271 --> 18:10.896
[demon brays]

18:22.730 --> 18:26.980
You see now the totality of your failure.

18:27.480 --> 18:33.480
Watching your world end around you
as you die on your father's sword,

18:33.563 --> 18:37.230
dipped in the blood
of the twin brother you abandoned.

18:37.313 --> 18:38.605
[panicked screaming]

18:47.313 --> 18:49.146
Motherfucker!

18:50.521 --> 18:51.521
Chamber still works.

18:52.230 --> 18:54.313
[steely, resolute music playing]

18:57.146 --> 18:58.146
One shot.

19:01.313 --> 19:03.730
[baby crying]

19:10.105 --> 19:13.438
All that inherited power,

19:13.521 --> 19:17.313
and it still wasn't enough to stop me!

19:17.396 --> 19:18.480
[sharp cry]

19:36.271 --> 19:37.855
[White Rabbit gagging]

19:48.021 --> 19:49.021
Jackpot.

19:57.730 --> 20:03.230
You shouldn't have told me about Vergil.

20:04.438 --> 20:08.605
I have to live for him!

20:08.688 --> 20:10.688
[dynamic, resolute music spiking]

20:12.855 --> 20:14.021
[Dante bellowing]

20:25.188 --> 20:26.313
[roaring]

20:27.313 --> 20:29.938
[Dante and White Rabbit's screams melding]

20:30.021 --> 20:32.105
[sonic boom crashing]

20:42.271 --> 20:43.271
[White Rabbit] Hmm.

20:44.480 --> 20:46.605
You believe you're on one side.

20:47.980 --> 20:49.521
The right one.

20:49.605 --> 20:50.730
But you're wrong.

20:51.688 --> 20:56.730
Eventually, you'll realize
you are welcomed by no one.

20:57.313 --> 21:01.063
An unlovable orphan.

21:01.146 --> 21:02.230
[Dante seethes]

21:02.313 --> 21:04.271
-[flesh rending]
-[Dante roars]

21:07.980 --> 21:10.146
[gurgling]

21:16.813 --> 21:19.021
[somber, mysterious music playing]

21:28.896 --> 21:30.188
[demon growling]

21:30.271 --> 21:31.563
[growling dissipates]

21:34.355 --> 21:36.355
[mysterious synth music warbles]

21:55.938 --> 21:56.938
[Dante panting]

22:15.813 --> 22:17.063
[Mary] This time…

22:17.563 --> 22:21.521
He's definitely fucking dead
this time… right?

22:22.730 --> 22:23.730
Definitely.

22:25.355 --> 22:26.355
Enzo?

22:27.063 --> 22:28.646
He seemed like a good guy.

22:29.146 --> 22:30.688
For a scumbag.

22:31.188 --> 22:32.188
He was.

22:33.396 --> 22:35.521
I think the Rabbit might have had a point.

22:35.605 --> 22:38.855
Not about letting demons
ravage the world and kill everybody.

22:39.355 --> 22:40.355
But the other stuff.

22:41.813 --> 22:44.980
Well, at least the world's still here.

22:45.063 --> 22:47.355
Don't sound too happy about it.

22:47.438 --> 22:49.896
You know me. I'm always happy.

22:50.646 --> 22:51.813
Right.

22:51.896 --> 22:53.813
Your jokes are a weak-shit cover.

22:53.896 --> 22:56.521
I've seen you in moments
when you think no one's looking.

22:56.605 --> 23:00.230
Did you do demon psychoanalysis classes
at DARKCOM or something?

23:00.313 --> 23:01.146
No.

23:02.063 --> 23:05.605
I've just had to watch everyone
I've ever cared about die in front of me.

23:06.813 --> 23:08.188
Me too.

23:08.980 --> 23:10.855
Or maybe I didn't.

23:11.855 --> 23:13.271
The Rabbit told me…

23:14.271 --> 23:16.480
He said my brother is still alive.

23:16.980 --> 23:18.855
You think it was true?

23:20.396 --> 23:21.396
No idea.

23:21.896 --> 23:23.980
Knowing there's even a chance,

23:24.063 --> 23:26.688
I have to go out there to try to find him.

23:27.896 --> 23:30.355
You, uh…
You could come with me if you want.

23:31.230 --> 23:33.355
We could do an odd couple buddy cop thing.

23:33.438 --> 23:34.563
Riggs and Murtaugh.

23:34.646 --> 23:35.855
Tango and Cash.

23:35.938 --> 23:38.855
-Dante and Lady.
-You know my name is Mary.

23:39.355 --> 23:41.188
[Dante] Yeah. I like Lady better.

23:41.271 --> 23:42.605
[Mary] Lady and Dante.

23:42.688 --> 23:44.063
Not Dante and Lady.

23:45.021 --> 23:46.271
Eh, we'll work on it.

23:50.021 --> 23:51.355
[Dante grunts]

23:51.855 --> 23:54.480
[uneasy, distressing music warbling]

23:54.563 --> 23:56.313
I still have to bring you in.

23:56.396 --> 23:57.813
Baines was right.

23:57.896 --> 23:59.355
With what your blood can do,

24:00.980 --> 24:05.396
it's too dangerous to have either you
or that sword out in the world.

24:06.230 --> 24:07.146
I'm sorry.

24:08.271 --> 24:10.563
[muffled explosion]

24:11.521 --> 24:13.521
[sinister synth music building]

24:17.438 --> 24:18.438
What now?

24:30.105 --> 24:33.438
I presume this is
the White Rabbit's device.

24:33.521 --> 24:37.021
The one that can detect
and hold open rifts between worlds.

24:37.605 --> 24:40.688
A hunk of pieced-together scrap.

24:40.771 --> 24:42.605
Mr. Vice President, sir. Good to see you.

24:42.688 --> 24:44.438
After the amulet heist,

24:44.521 --> 24:46.646
I knew there must be a leak.

24:46.730 --> 24:49.730
My agents have had
the DARKCOM building under surveillance.

24:50.230 --> 24:53.146
Every room, every call.

24:54.396 --> 24:55.563
I didn't have a choice.

24:56.563 --> 24:58.646
He was watching my daughters.

24:58.730 --> 25:01.855
If I didn't do what he said,
he would have…

25:01.938 --> 25:06.480
So, you agreed to help him
unleash Hell on Earth.

25:06.563 --> 25:07.396
[disbelieving laugh]

25:07.480 --> 25:10.771
You think Hell on Earth would be
that different from my life now?

25:10.855 --> 25:13.521
I did what I had to do to protect my kids.

25:13.605 --> 25:15.355
This world ain't ever
give a damn about us.

25:15.438 --> 25:17.480
Even I, for much of my life,

25:17.563 --> 25:20.146
could not comprehend his true plan.

25:21.021 --> 25:25.355
God has never asked us to sit idly by
and await his kingdom on Earth,

25:25.438 --> 25:27.563
but to build it ourselves.

25:28.980 --> 25:32.313
This device, what did the Rabbit
want you to do with it?

25:33.063 --> 25:34.063
He told me…

25:35.813 --> 25:37.063
He told me to destroy it.

25:37.146 --> 25:39.230
He wanted to keep his tech
out of human hands,

25:39.313 --> 25:41.021
so we couldn't use it against them.

25:41.105 --> 25:44.063
Then the Devil is
as clever as his reputation.

25:45.063 --> 25:47.188
We are going to use it, Anders.

25:47.896 --> 25:51.480
To wage the final war against Hell itself.

25:51.563 --> 25:52.646
[Anders laughs in disbelief]

25:53.730 --> 25:56.230
You really are out of your goddamn mind.

25:56.313 --> 25:58.730
You think you can win a war with Hell?

25:58.813 --> 26:01.271
My faith in the Lord is absolute.

26:01.355 --> 26:06.188
I fell from an aircraft with nothing,
and still, he saved me.

26:06.896 --> 26:09.980
Let's see if the Devil
does the same for you.

26:12.855 --> 26:14.896
[screaming]

26:19.480 --> 26:21.480
[unearthly quavering]

26:24.605 --> 26:26.896
Scramble the jets on my position.

26:27.396 --> 26:30.938
Operation Inferno has started.

26:31.021 --> 26:33.230
["American Idiot" by Green Day playing]

26:33.730 --> 26:35.980
[rollicking pop-punk music playing]

26:38.813 --> 26:41.688
♪ Don't wanna be an American idiot ♪

26:44.063 --> 26:46.521
♪ Don't want a nation
Under the new media ♪

26:49.146 --> 26:51.688
♪ And can you hear the sound of hysteria ♪

26:54.230 --> 26:56.938
♪ The subliminal mindfuck America ♪

26:59.563 --> 27:02.230
♪ Welcome to a new kind of tension ♪

27:02.313 --> 27:05.063
♪ All across the alienation ♪

27:05.146 --> 27:08.521
♪ Where everything isn't
Meant to be okay ♪

27:09.855 --> 27:12.688
♪ Television dreams of tomorrow ♪

27:12.771 --> 27:15.188
♪ We're not the ones
Who're meant to follow ♪

27:15.271 --> 27:17.688
♪ For that's enough to argue ♪

27:25.438 --> 27:28.021
♪ Now everybody do the propaganda ♪

27:30.521 --> 27:33.230
♪ And sing along to the age of paranoia ♪

27:39.730 --> 27:41.688
[president] My fellow Americans.

27:42.730 --> 27:47.313
What I am about to tell you
is going to sound shocking.

27:47.813 --> 27:50.146
Even unbelievable.

27:50.730 --> 27:52.480
But as your president,

27:53.688 --> 27:58.855
it is my duty
not to conceal these hard truths,

27:59.813 --> 28:01.646
but to lay them before you

28:02.146 --> 28:07.896
so we may confront them
together as a nation.

28:08.605 --> 28:10.438
The truth is,

28:11.813 --> 28:13.855
Hell is real.

28:15.063 --> 28:18.021
Demons are real.

28:18.771 --> 28:19.688
[song halts]

28:19.771 --> 28:21.105
[foreboding music droning]

28:30.355 --> 28:31.355
[distant explosion]

28:33.188 --> 28:35.105
-[klaxon wailing]
-[bursts of gunfire]

28:35.188 --> 28:37.146
-[guard yells]
-[blade rasping]

28:37.230 --> 28:39.146
[guards screaming in panic]

28:51.105 --> 28:53.521
[knight] Our King Mundus
grants you your freedom.

28:54.521 --> 28:56.021
Show him gratitude.

28:56.771 --> 29:00.105
It was Mundus who freed me
from my own bondage.

29:01.896 --> 29:02.896
[power rushing]

29:06.480 --> 29:08.896
The sapiens and their armies

29:08.980 --> 29:11.605
aren't aware of the storm they ride into.

29:13.313 --> 29:15.230
I am that storm.

29:16.563 --> 29:21.563
-["Bury the Light" playing]
-♪ I am the storm that is approaching ♪

29:21.646 --> 29:23.688
♪ Provoking ♪

29:23.771 --> 29:27.688
♪ Black clouds in isolation ♪

29:28.188 --> 29:33.605
♪ I am reclaimer of my name ♪

29:33.688 --> 29:35.063
♪ Born in flames ♪

29:35.146 --> 29:36.563
♪ I have been blessed ♪

29:36.646 --> 29:40.188
♪ My family crest is a demon of death ♪

29:40.271 --> 29:42.438
[dark, brooding goth metal playing]

30:06.146 --> 30:11.646
♪ Beyond the tree ♪

30:11.730 --> 30:15.438
♪ Fire burns ♪

30:15.521 --> 30:17.021
IN MEMORY OF KEVIN CONROY
(1955-2022)

30:17.521 --> 30:23.396
♪ Secret love ♪

30:23.480 --> 30:29.230
♪ Bloodline yearns ♪